    "summary": "Repair PR #90273 in place by addressing Copilot's actionable review comments in src/infra/fs-safe.test.ts: move or defer the hardlink capability probe so test-file module evaluation does not perform synchronous filesystem I/O, and ensure temporary directory creation and cleanup are covered by the guarded probe path.",
    "pr_title": "test: make fs-safe hardlink tests compatible with Windows",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nRepairs #90273 so the Windows hardlink capability tests remain portable without doing fragile filesystem work at module import time.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nCopilot flagged two actionable issues in the current PR head: `mkdtempSync` can throw before the probe is guarded, and synchronous filesystem probing during module evaluation can make test-file loading depend on environment filesystem latency.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTest-only change. It keeps the contributor's intended Windows coverage improvement while making the probe safer for constrained or slow test environments.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Source PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/90273 by @aniruddhaadak80\n- Expected validation: `pnpm check:changed -- src/infra/fs-safe.test.ts`\n- Review-bot findings to address: Copilot comments on guarded temp dir creation and import-time synchronous filesystem I/O",
